{"metadata":{"externalID":"Tuplé","roleHeading":"Framework","symbolKind":"module","modules":[{"name":"Tuplé"}],"role":"collection","title":"Tuplé"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tuple-\/Type-Aliases","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tuple-\/Properties","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tuple-\/Instance-Methods","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tuple-\/Type","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/Swift\/Sequence"],"anchor":"Topics"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Bridge the gap between tuples and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/collections","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Despite tuples being very much like fixed-count arrays, they are not equipped with much of the built-in functionality that is provided for any type of collection in the standard library. ☹️"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This package addresses some of the omissions, bringing tuples and collections closer to feature parity."}]},{"anchor":"Geneity","type":"heading","level":4,"text":"“Geneity”"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Swift’s collections are homogeneous, meaning they’re generic over their "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/collection\/element","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Some of what’s in this package does require the tuples you’re working with to be homogeneous, as well."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"But it’s generally no more complex to support working with heterogeneous tuples, so this package defers to the choice of maximum versatility, supporting homogeneous tuples as a subset of heterogenous ones.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, the code for reversing an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(Int, String)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["reversed((1, \"Two\"))"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"…also supports "},{"code":"(Int, Int)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["reversed((1, 2))"]},{"level":4,"text":"Element Count","type":"heading","anchor":"Element-Count"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This package will support arbitrary-count tuples, incorporating the evolution of "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-evolution\/blob\/main\/proposals\/0393-parameter-packs.md","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", when possible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Otherwise, the cap for support is tuples with "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"4 elements"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":". This is the de facto size limit found in 3D graphics frameworks such as "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/realitykit","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and libraries such as "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/simd-vector-types"},{"type":"text","text":" and  "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/spatial"},{"text":". Supporting visionOS development by filling in tuple-shaped holes in that Apple-provided software is a primary motivator for this package, but it is otherwise unrelated to graphics.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Usage Examples","type":"heading","anchor":"Usage-Examples","level":5},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You’ve got the source code, so aside from reading this documentation, see the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tests"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" folder for example usage! 😺","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/tupl-"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swift/collection/element":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/collection\/element","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Element"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/collection\/element","type":"link","title":"Element"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/spatial":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/spatial","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Spatial","type":"text"}],"type":"link","title":"Spatial","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/spatial"},"doc://xn--tupl-epa/documentation/Tupl-/Swift/Sequence":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Tuples created from some of the elements of sequences."}],"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Sequence"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/Swift\/Sequence","kind":"symbol","title":"Sequence","url":"\/documentation\/tupl-\/swift\/sequence","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Sequence","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swift/collections":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/collections","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Collections"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/collections","type":"link","title":"Collections"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swift/simd-vector-types":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/docume